frank
direct and unreserved in speech

cook
to prepare (food) by the use of heat, as by boiling, baking, or roasting.

important
of much or great significance or consequence

adult
a person who is fully grown or developed or of age.

distributor
a person or thing that distributes

taste
to try or test the flavor or quality of (something) by taking some into the mouth

conversation
informal interchange of thoughts, information, etc., by spoken words; oral communication between persons

peace
the nonwarring condition of a nation, group of nations, or the world.

knit
to join closely and firmly, as members or parts

arrest
to seize (a person) by legal authority or warrant

denial
an assertion that something said or believed is false

tease
to irritate or provoke with persistent petty distractions, trifling jests, or other annoyances, often in a playful way

determine
to conclude or ascertain, as after reasoning, observation, etc.

assertive
confidently aggressive or self-assured

restoration
the act of restoring

